      "created_at": "2016-03-09 19:37:39 UTC",
      "updated_at": "2016-03-09 19:37:39 UTC",
      "body": "I made a special case if you use the Scala.js style AND `js.native` is the rhs of an assignment (def/val/var)."
    }
  ],
  "created_at": "2016-03-09 10:18:26 UTC",
  "updated_at": "2016-03-10 12:45:49 UTC",
  "closed_at": "2016-03-10 12:45:45 UTC",
  "body": "Note that this is not a question of preference of the Scala.js style guide. It should apply equally to all style guides, but it's specific to Scala.js code. The `= js.native` is a very special beast.\r\n\r\nOriginal:\r\n```scala\r\n  def uniform4fv(location: WebGLUniformLocation, v: Float32Array): Unit = js.native\r\n```\r\n\r\nScalafmt:\r\n```scala\r\n  def uniform4fv(location: WebGLUniformLocation, v: Float32Array): Unit =\r\n    js.native\r\n```\r\n\r\nI would like the input to look like this:\r\n```scala\r\n  def uniform4fv(location: WebGLUniformLocation,\r\n      v: Float32Array): Unit = js.native\r\n```\r\nIn all cases, `js.native` should be kept right next to its `=`. Which means that the line should be broken somewhere else.\r\n\r\nUsing\r\n* 0.1.1\r\n* default\r\n"
}